main event: Multiple unidentified objects were observed over Roswell, New Mexico on November 24, 1960. The objects were described as disc-shaped with yellowish borders, traveling at an extremely high speed.
interesting points: The objects were not in contact with each other and would suddenly appear and disappear from the radar screen.
The objects were observed at an elevation of 60-70 degrees, moving in a southerly direction.
The objects were observed for approximately 3 minutes.
Similar unidentified objects were sighted over Roswell, New Mexico on October 31, 1956, described as a brilliant light the size of a baseball moving erratically.
The 1950 sighting at Holloman AFB in New Mexico described two oval-shaped, bluish-white lights that were motionless and silent.
sighted object: disc-shaped objects with yellowish borders, and oval-shaped bluish-white lights
location: Roswell, New Mexico; Holloman AFB, New Mexico
photographs: no photographs included in the reports
